```go
func (fs *UnixFS) fchmodat(op string, dirfd int, name string, mode FileMode) error {
   return ensurePathError(unix.Fchmodat(dirfd, name, uint32(mode), 0), op, name)
}
```

This call to the unix function `fchmodat(int fd, char* name, mode_t mode, int flags)`  does not have the flag `AT_SYMLINK_NOFOLLOW` set, and Wings neither checks or validate if the target file is a symlink. This allows one to change permissions of files or folders outside of the server container by making symlinks to existing files in the host and then chmoding it.", "ghsa_id": "GHSA-rhq6-9rgh-v45c", "github_reviewed_at": "2026-06-26T20:53:00Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-rhq6-9rgh-v45c", "identifiers": [{"type": "GHSA", "value": "GHSA-rhq6-9rgh-v45c"}], "nvd_published_at": null, "published_at": "2026-06-26T20:53:00Z", "references": ["https://github.com/pterodactyl/wings/security/advisories/GHSA-rhq6-9rgh-v45c", "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-rhq6-9rgh-v45c"], "repository_advisory_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pterodactyl/wings/security-advisories/GHSA-rhq6-9rgh-v45c", "severity": "medium", "source_code_location": "https://github.com/pterodactyl/wings", "summary": "Pterodactyl Wings: Chmod operation can be used to change permissions of files outside of the server container", "type": "reviewed", "updated_at": "2026-06-26T20:53:03Z", "url": "https://api.github.com/advisories/GHSA-rhq6-9rgh-v45c", "vulnerabilities": [{"first_patched_version": "1.12.2", "package": {"ecosystem": "go", "name": "github.com/pterodactyl/wings"}, "vulnerable_functions": [], "vulnerable_version_range": ">= 1.11.9, < 1.12.2"}], "withdrawn_at": null}
